fields.field_context_on_pdf: 1. Tell us about yourself. 1a. Your Social Security Number (or your Medicare Number)
1b. Your name (last name, first name, middle name)
1c. Name at birth if different than item 1b
1f. State or country of birth (spell out - no abbreviations)
1g. Mailing address (number and street, PO Box, or route)
1h. Address of permanent residence, if different from your mailing address
2. Tell us about your earnings and work history. 2a. How much were your total earnings last year? Enter the total amount of your W2 wages and net earnings. If none, write “NONE.”
2b. How much do you expect your total earnings to be this year? If none, write “NONE.”
2c. Did you or your spouse (or former spouse) work in the railroad industry for 5 years or more? (If no, skip the marriage questions in item 4.) Select here for Yes.
2d. Are you a dependent child using your parent’s work history or Social Security/Railroad Retirement Board insured status to qualify for ESRD benefits? Select here for Yes.
Mother's Date of Birth. 2 digit month
Mother's Social Security Number. first 3 digits
Mother's Railroad Retirement Board (RRB) Number. First 4 dsigits
Father's Date of Birth. 2 digit month
Father's Social Security Number. first 3 digits
Father's Railroad Retirement Board (RRB) Number. First 4 dsigits
e. Have either of your parents worked in the railroad industry for 5 years or more? Select here for yes.
3. Tell us your citizenship. 3a. Are you a United States citizen? (If yes, go to item 4.) Select here for male.
3b. Are you lawfully present in the U.S.? (If no, go to item 4.) Select here for Yes.
3c. When did you become lawfully present in the U.S.? 2 digit month
3d. Are you currently a resident of the U.S.? Select here for yes.
3e. When did you become a resident of the U.S.?  2 digit month
3f. Have you resided in the U.S. without a break for the past 5 years? Select here for yes.
3g. Enter where you lived for the last 5 years and the dates you lived there. (If you need more space, add the information to the remarks space in Section 7.) Address 1
4. Tell us about your marital status. 4a. Are you currently married? (If no, go to item 4g.) Select here for yes.
4b. Spouse’s name (last name, first name, middle name)
4c. Spouse’s date of birth. 2 digit month
4d. Spouse’s Social Security Number. First 3 digits
4f. Does your spouse (or did your spouse) work for a railroad or get railroad benefits? Select here for yes.
4g. If you’re not married now, did you have a former marriage that lasted 10 or more years OR ended in death? (If no, go to item 5.) Select here for yes.
4h. Name of former spouse (last name, first name, middle name)
4i. Former spouse’s date of birth. 2 digit month
4j. Former spouse’s Social Security Number. First 3 digits
4k. Date of former marriage. 2 digit month
4l. Date former marriage ended. 2 digit month
4m. Date of former spouse’s death, if deceased. 2 digit month

4n. Do you have another marriage that lasted 10 years or ended in death? (If you need more space to add another former spouse’s name, date of birth, SSN, marriage start and end dates, or the former spouse’s date of death, add the information in Section 7 Remarks.)  Select here for yes.
5. Tell us about your medical history. 5a. Have you received regularly scheduled dialysis? (If no, go to item 5e.)Select here for yes.
5b. When did dialysis begin? 2 digit month
5c. Has dialysis ended? (If no, go to item 5e.) Select here for yes.
5d. When did dialysis end? 2 digit month
5e. Have you participated in (or do you expect to participate in) a  Select here for yes.
5f. When did you start or when do you plan to start participation in a self-dialysis training program? 2 digit month
5g. Have you received a kidney transplant? (If no, go to item 6) Select here for yes.
5h. Enter date(s) of transplant(s). 2 digit month
5i. Were you in the hospital for related procedures the month before you got the kidney transplant? (If no, go to item 6.) Select here for yes.
5j. Enter date(s) of hospitalization. 2 digit month
6. Enrollment in Medicare Part B. 6a. Do you want to sign up for Medicare Part B? (You pay a monthly premium for Part B. If no, go to item 7). Select here for yes.

6b. If your application is processed within 5 months after the first month in which you meet the requirements for Medicare, your coverage will start that first month. If your application is processed more than 5 months after the first month in which you meet the requirements, you can choose one of the following for your first month of coverage. (Please check one.) Select here for The earliest possible month (you must pay all premiums for any past months of coverage)
Or select here for: The month this application is filed
Or select here for: The month this application is processed
8. Sign your application. 8a. If you’re completing this application for someone else, what’s your name and your relationship to the person applying?
8d. Name of witness (first and last name)
